  "prompt": "How can fetch the data from differente table of mysql database in my app? I can only fetch the data from only one table using url connection!",
  "response": "Here are several approaches to fetch data from multiple MySQL tables in an app:\n\n1. Multiple Separate Queries:\n```java\npublic void fetchMultipleTableData() {\n    try {\n        Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url, username, password);\n        \n        // Query for first table\n        String query1 = \"SELECT * FROM table1\";\n        PreparedStatement statement1 = connection.prepareStatement(query1);\n        ResultSet resultSet1 = statement1.executeQuery();\n        \n        // Query for second table\n        String query2 = \"SELECT * FROM table2\";\n        PreparedStatement statement2 = connection.prepareStatement(query2);\n        ResultSet resultSet2 = statement2.executeQuery();\n    } catch (SQLException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n2. JOIN Query:\n```java\npublic void fetchJoinedData() {\n    try {\n        Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url, username, password);\n        \n        // Join query to fetch data from multiple tables\n        String joinQuery = \"SELECT t1.column1, t1.column2, t2.column3 \" +\n                           \"FROM table1 t1 \" +\n                           \"JOIN table2 t2 ON t1.id = t2.id\";\n        \n        PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(joinQuery);\n        ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery();\n        \n        while (resultSet.next()) {\n            // Process joined data\n            String column1 = resultSet.getString(\"column1\");\n            String column2 = resultSet.getString(\"column2\");\n            String column3 = resultSet.getString(\"column3\");\n        }\n    } catch (SQLException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n3. Subquery Approach:\n```java\npublic void fetchUsingSubquery() {\n    try {\n        Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url, username, password);\n        \n        // Subquery to fetch related data\n        String subqueryQuery = \"SELECT t1.*, \" +\n                               \"(SELECT column FROM table2 WHERE table2.id = table1.id) AS related_column \" +\n                               \"FROM table1\";\n        \n        PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(subqueryQuery);\n        ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery();\n    } catch (SQLException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n4. Using DAO Pattern:\n```java\npublic class DatabaseHelper {\n    private Connection connection;\n    \n    public List<DataModel> fetchMultiTableData() {\n        List<DataModel> dataList = new ArrayList<>();\n        try {\n            connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url, username, password);\n            \n            String query = \"SELECT t1.*, t2.* FROM table1 t1 \" +\n                           \"LEFT JOIN table2 t2 ON t1.id = t2.id\";\n            \n            PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(query);\n            ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery();\n            \n            while (resultSet.next()) {\n                DataModel data = new DataModel();\n                data.setColumn1(resultSet.getString(\"t1.column1\"));\n                data.setColumn2(resultSet.getString(\"t2.column2\"));\n                dataList.add(data);\n            }\n        } catch (SQLException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        } finally {\n            closeConnection();\n        }\n        return dataList;\n    }\n    \n    private void closeConnection() {\n        try {\n            if (connection != null) {\n                connection.close();\n            }\n        } catch (SQLException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n5. Using ORM (Object-Relational Mapping):\n```java\n// Using Hibernate example\npublic List<YourEntity> fetchMultiTableData() {\n    Session session = sessionFactory.openSession();\n    try {\n        // Using HQL or Criteria API\n        Query query = session.createQuery(\n            \"FROM YourEntity e JOIN e.relatedEntity re\"\n        );\n        List<YourEntity> results = query.list();\n        return results;\n    } finally {\n        session.close();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nBest Practices:\n1. Always use PreparedStatement to prevent SQL injection\n2. Close database connections after use\n3. Handle exceptions properly\n4. Consider connection pooling for performance\n5. Use try-with-resources for automatic resource management\n\nAdditional Tips:\n- Choose the right approach based on your specific use case\n- Consider performance implications of different query types\n- Use indexes on join columns for better performance\n- Limit the number of columns retrieved if possible\n\nRecommended Libraries:\n- JDBC for direct database access\n- Hibernate for ORM\n- Spring Data JPA for simplified database operations\n- MyBatis for SQL mapping\n\nExample Connection Setup:\n```java\nString url = \"jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/yourdatabase\";\nString username = \"your_username\";\nString password = \"your_password\";\n\n// Ensure you have MySQL connector in your classpath\nClass.forName(\"com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver\");\n```\n\nChoose the approach that best fits your specific application architecture and requirements. Each method has its pros and cons depending on your use case.",
